High-ranking  political office bearers take home the same salaries this year, for the third year in a row. President Cyril Ramaphosa signed off and gazetted the salaries this week. This year, National Assembly speaker, the chair of the National Council of Provinces (NCOP) and the deputy president are entitled to a salary package of R2,825,470. Each package is inclusive of a basic salary, which is 60% of the total package. Below are the remunerations of members of the National Assembly and permanent delegates of the National Council of Provinces: Parliament Provincial legislatures The president's salary, which is R2.99m, still needs to be accepted by parliament. TimesLIVE